{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The unfairness in Ferguson\u2019s court system that is highlighted by a Justice Department report is not limited to it or even to Missouri.", "abstract": "Justice Dept officials and some advocates say report that found government of Ferguson, Mo, to be unfair in its treatment of blacks and the poor should be read by police and city officials across the country; while Ferguson was singled out, many cities in Missouri display similar troubling patterns in way police and court systems are run, and lawsuits and investigations across country have focused on how justice system places inordinate burden on poor.", "section_name": "U.S.", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Campbell", "role": "reported", "lastname": "ROBERTSON", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}, {"firstname": "Shaila", "role": "reported", "lastname": "DEWAN", "rank": 2, "organization": ""}, {"firstname": "Matt", "role": "reported", "lastname": "APUZZO", "rank": 3, "organization": ""}], "original": "By CAMPBELL ROBERTSON, SHAILA DEWAN and MATT APUZZO", "contributor": "Campbell Robertson reported from New Orleans, Shaila Dewan from New York and Matt Apuzzo from Washington."}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/08/us/ferguson-became-symbol-but-bias-knows-no-border.html", "lead_paragraph": "The unfairness in Ferguson\u2019s court system that is highlighted by a Justice Department report is not limited to it or even to Missouri.", "headline": {"main": "Ferguson Became Symbol, but Bias Knows No Border", "print_headline": "Ferguson Became Symbol of an Ill Plaguing the U.S."}, "_id": "54fb9db238f0d80a0a50021f", "word_count": "1525", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/03/08/us/08ferguson-JP-01/08ferguson-JP-01-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/03/08/us/08ferguson-JP-01/08ferguson-JP-01-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"